29/* Table for Big5 to UCS conversion.
30
31 With HKSCS mappings 0x8140-0xA0FE and 0xFA40-0xFEFE added; more info:
32 http://www.ogcio.gov.hk/en/business/tech_promotion/ccli/hkscs/
33
34 Using the charmap:
35
36 sed 's|^%IRREVERSIBLE%||' BIG5-HKSCS |
37 sed 's|^<U0*\(.....*\)> *.x\(..\)/x\(..\).*|0x\2\3 \1|p;d' |
38 perl big5.pl
39
40 where big5.pl is:
41
42 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
43 while (<>) {
44 local($big5, $ucs) = split;
45 $big5 = hex($big5) - 0x8740;
46 local($ridx) = int($big5 / 256) * 195 + $big5 % 256;
47 printf "\n " if (($n % 4) == 0);
48 ++$n;
49 printf " [%5d] = 0x%s,", $ridx, $ucs;
50 }
51 print "\n";
52 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
53*/

17623/* This is the index table for the one above. It's generated with:
17624
17625 sed 's|^<U\(....\)>|<U0000\1>|' BIG5-HKSCS |
17626 sort | sed 's|^<U0*\(.....*\)> *./x\(..\)/x\(..\).*|\1 \2\3|p;d' |
17627 perl big5.pl
17628
17629 where big5.pl is:
17630 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
17631 $first=0;
17632 $old=0x00;
17633 $offset = -1;
17634 while (<>) {
17635 local($ucs, $big5) = split;
17636 $big5 = hex($big5);
17637 $ucs = hex($ucs);
17638 if ($ucs - $old >= 128) {
17639 if ($first != 0) {
17640 printf (" { 0x%04x, 0x%04x, %5d },\n", $first, $old,
17641 $offset - ($old - $first));
17642 }
17643 $first = $ucs;
17644 } else {
17645 while ($old + 1 < $ucs) {
17646 ++$old;
17647 ++$offset;
17648 }
17649 }
17650 $old=$ucs;
17651 ++$offset;
17652 }
17653 printf (" { 0x%04x, 0x%04x, %5d },\n", $first, $old,
17654 $offset - ($old - $first));
17655 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
17656 */
17657static struct

17735/* Definitions used in the body of the `gconv' function. */
17736#define CHARSET_NAME "BIG5HKSCS//"
17737#define FROM_LOOP from_big5hkscs
17738#define TO_LOOP to_big5hkscs
17739#define DEFINE_INIT 1
17740#define DEFINE_FINI 1
17741#define ONE_DIRECTION 0
17742#define FROM_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_FROM 1
17743#define FROM_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_FROM 2
17744#define FROM_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_TO 4
17745#define FROM_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_TO 8
17746#define TO_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_FROM 4
17747#define TO_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_FROM 4
17748#define TO_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_TO 1
17749#define TO_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_TO 2
17750#define PREPARE_LOOP \
17751 int saved_state; \
17752 int *statep = &data->__statep->__count;
17753#define EXTRA_LOOP_ARGS , statep
17754
17755
17756/* Since we might have to reset input pointer we must be able to save
17757 and restore the state. */
17758#define SAVE_RESET_STATE(Save) \
17759 if (Save) \
17760 saved_state = *statep; \
17761 else \
17762 *statep = saved_state
17763
17764
17765/* During BIG5-HKSCS to UCS-4 conversion, the COUNT element of the state
17766 contains the last UCS-4 character, shifted by 3 bits.
17767 During UCS-4 to BIG5-HKSCS conversion, the COUNT element of the state
17768 contains the last two bytes to be output, shifted by 3 bits. */
17769
17770/* Since this is a stateful encoding we have to provide code which resets
17771 the output state to the initial state. This has to be done during the
17772 flushing. */
17773#define EMIT_SHIFT_TO_INIT \
17774 if (data->__statep->__count != 0) \
17775 { \
17776 if (FROM_DIRECTION) \
17777 { \
17778 if (__glibc_likely (outbuf + 4 <= outend)) \
17779 { \
17780 /* Write out the last character. */ \
17781 *((uint32_t *) outbuf) = data->__statep->__count >> 3; \
17782 outbuf += sizeof (uint32_t); \
17783 data->__statep->__count = 0; \
17784 } \
17785 else \
17786 /* We don't have enough room in the output buffer. */ \
17787 status = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT; \
17788 } \
17789 else \
17790 { \
17791 if (__glibc_likely (outbuf + 2 <= outend)) \
17792 { \
17793 /* Write out the last character. */ \
17794 uint32_t lasttwo = data->__statep->__count >> 3; \
17795 *outbuf++ = (lasttwo >> 8) & 0xff; \
17796 *outbuf++ = lasttwo & 0xff; \
17797 data->__statep->__count = 0; \
17798 } \
17799 else \
17800 /* We don't have enough room in the output buffer. */ \
17801 status = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT; \
17802 } \
17803 }
17804
17805
17806/* First define the conversion function from Big5 to UCS4. */
17807#define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT FROM_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_FROM
17808#define MAX_NEEDED_INPUT FROM_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_FROM
17809#define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT FROM_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_TO
17810#define MAX_NEEDED_OUTPUT FROM_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_TO
17811#define LOOPFCT FROM_LOOP
17812#define BODY \
17813 { \
17814 uint32_t ch; \
17815 \
17816 /* Determine whether there is a buffered character pending. */ \
17817 ch = *statep >> 3; \
17818 if (__glibc_likely (ch == 0)) \
17819 { \
17820 /* No - so look at the next input byte. */ \
17821 ch = *inptr; \
17822 \
17823 if (ch >= 0x81 && ch <= 0xfe) \
17824 { \
17825 /* Two-byte character. First test whether the next byte \
17826 is also available. */ \
17827 uint32_t ch2; \
17828 int idx; \
17829 \
17830 if (__glibc_unlikely (inptr + 1 >= inend)) \
17831 { \
17832 /* The second character is not available. */ \
17833 result = __GCONV_INCOMPLETE_INPUT; \
17834 break; \
17835 } \
17836 \
17837 ch2 = inptr[1]; \
17838 idx = (ch - 0x87) * 195 + ch2 - 0x40; \
17839 /* See whether the second byte is in the correct range. */ \
17840 if (ch < 0x87 || ch2 < 0x40 || ch2 > 0xfe \
17841 || (ch = big5hkscs_to_ucs[idx]) == 0) \
17842 { \
17843 /* Check for special cases: combining characters. */ \
17844 if (idx == 195 + 0x22 /* 8862 */) \
17845 { \
17846 ch = 0xca; \
17847 ch2 = 0x304; \
17848 } \
17849 else if (idx == 195 + 0x24 /* 8864 */) \
17850 { \
17851 ch = 0xca; \
17852 ch2 = 0x30c; \
17853 } \
17854 else if (idx == 195 + 0x63 /* 88a3 */) \
17855 { \
17856 ch = 0xea; \
17857 ch2 = 0x304; \
17858 } \
17859 else if (idx == 195 + 0x65 /* 88a5 */) \
17860 { \
17861 ch = 0xea; \
17862 ch2 = 0x30c; \
17863 } \
17864 else \
17865 /* This is illegal. */ \
17866 STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1); \
17867 \
17868 inptr += 2; \
17869 \
17870 put32 (outptr, ch); \
17871 outptr += 4; \
17872 \
17873 /* See whether we have room for two characters. */ \
17874 if (outptr + 4 <= outend) \
17875 { \
17876 put32 (outptr, ch2); \
17877 outptr += 4; \
17878 continue; \
17879 } \
17880 \
17881 /* Otherwise store only the first character now, and \
17882 put the second one into the queue. */ \
17883 *statep = ch2 << 3; \
17884 /* Tell the caller why we terminate the loop. */ \
17885 result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT; \
17886 break; \
17887 } \
17888 \
17889 inptr += 2; \
17890 } \
17891 else if (__glibc_unlikely (ch == 0xff)) \
17892 { \
17893 STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1); \
17894 } \
17895 else \
17896 ++inptr; \
17897 } \
17898 \
17899 put32 (outptr, ch); \
17900 outptr += 4; \
17901 }
17902#define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
17903#define EXTRA_LOOP_DECLS , int *statep
17904#define ONEBYTE_BODY \
17905 { \
17906 if (c <= 0x80) \
17907 return c; \
17908 else \
17909 return WEOF; \
17910 }
17911#include <iconv/loop.c>
17912
17913
17914/* Next, define the other direction. */
17915#define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT TO_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_FROM
17916#define MAX_NEEDED_INPUT TO_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_FROM
17917#define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT TO_LOOP_MIN_NEEDED_TO
17918#define MAX_NEEDED_OUTPUT TO_LOOP_MAX_NEEDED_TO
17919#define LOOPFCT TO_LOOP
17920#define BODY \
17921 { \
17922 uint32_t ch = get32 (inptr); \
17923 \
17924 if ((*statep >> 3) != 0) \
17925 { \
17926 /* Attempt to combine the last character with this one. */ \
17927 uint16_t lasttwo = *statep >> 3; \
17928 \
17929 if (ch == 0x304 && lasttwo == 0x8866) \
17930 ch = 0x8862; \
17931 else if (ch == 0x30c && lasttwo == 0x8866) \
17932 ch = 0x8864; \
17933 else if (ch == 0x304 && lasttwo == 0x88a7) \
17934 ch = 0x88a3; \
17935 else if (ch == 0x30c && lasttwo == 0x88a7) \
17936 ch = 0x88a5; \
17937 else \
17938 goto not_combining; \
17939 \
17940 /* Output the combined character. */ \
17941 if (__glibc_unlikely (outptr + 1 >= outend)) \
17942 { \
17943 result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT; \
17944 break; \
17945 } \
17946 *outptr++ = (ch >> 8) & 0xff; \
17947 *outptr++ = ch & 0xff; \
17948 *statep = 0; \
17949 inptr += 4; \
17950 continue; \
17951 \
17952 not_combining: \
17953 /* Output the buffered character. */ \
17954 if (__glibc_unlikely (outptr + 1 >= outend)) \
17955 { \
17956 result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT; \
17957 break; \
17958 } \
17959 *outptr++ = (lasttwo >> 8) & 0xff; \
17960 *outptr++ = lasttwo & 0xff; \
17961 *statep = 0; \
17962 continue; \
17963 } \
17964 \
17965 if (ch <= 0x0080) \
17966 *outptr++ = ch; \
17967 else \
17968 { \
17969 const unsigned char *cp = (const unsigned char *) ""; \
17970 size_t i; \
17971 \
17972 for (i = 0; \
17973 i < sizeof (from_ucs4_idx) / sizeof (from_ucs4_idx[0]); \
17974 ++i) \
17975 { \
17976 if (ch < from_ucs4_idx[i].from) \
17977 break; \
17978 if (from_ucs4_idx[i].to >= ch) \
17979 { \
17980 cp = from_ucs4[from_ucs4_idx[i].offset \
17981 + ch - from_ucs4_idx[i].from]; \
17982 break; \
17983 } \
17984 } \
17985 \
17986 if (cp[0] == '\0') \
17987 { \
17988 UNICODE_TAG_HANDLER (ch, 4); \
17989 \
17990 /* Illegal character. */ \
17991 STANDARD_TO_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (4); \
17992 } \
17993 else \
17994 { \
17995 /* Check for possible combining character. */ \
17996 if (__glibc_unlikely (ch == 0xca || ch == 0xea)) \
17997 { \
17998 *statep = ((cp[0] << 8) | cp[1]) << 3; \
17999 inptr += 4; \
18000 continue; \
18001 } \
18002 \
18003 /* See whether there is enough room to write the second byte. */ \
18004 if (__builtin_expect (cp[1] != '\0', 1) \
18005 && __builtin_expect (outptr + 1 >= outend, 0)) \
18006 { \
18007 /* We have not enough room. */ \
18008 result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT; \
18009 break; \
18010 } \
18011 \
18012 *outptr++ = cp[0]; \
18013 if (__glibc_likely (cp[1] != '\0')) \
18014 *outptr++ = cp[1]; \
18015 } \
18016 } \
18017 \
18018 inptr += 4; \
18019 }
18020#define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
18021#define EXTRA_LOOP_DECLS , int *statep
18022#include <iconv/loop.c>
